OL,5, The job of minister for disabled people
OL,6, has been downgraded, with the new      
OL,7, holder of the position staying at the  
OL,8, most junior level in government.       
OL,10,FMims Davies has taken on the role      
OL,11,Fwithin the Department for Work and     
OL,12,FPensions (DWP), but remains a          
OL,13,Fparliamentary under secretary of state.
OL,15,FPredecessor Tom Pursglove was a        
OL,16,Fminister of state when he held the job.
OL,18,FEarlier, No 10 denied the role was     
OL,19,Fbeing downgraded as charities called   
OL,20,Ffor a new minister to be brought in.   
